then consider p being (FinSequence of K) such that A3: ( len p ) = ( len M1 ) and A4: M1 is_col_circulant_about p by CKB10:def 1;
p is (Element of ( ( len p ) -tuples_on (the carrier of K) )) by FINSEQ_2:92;
then A5: ( - p ) is (Element of ( ( len p ) -tuples_on (the carrier of K) )) by FINSEQ_2:113;
then A6: (( len ( - M1 ) ) = n & ( len ( - p ) ) = ( len p )) by CARD_1:def 7,MATRIX_1:24;
A7: ( len M1 ) = n by MATRIX_1:24;
then A8: ( dom p ) = ( Seg n ) by A3,FINSEQ_1:def 3;
(for i,j being Nat holds ([ i,j ] in ( Indices ( - M1 ) ) implies ( ( - M1 ) * (i,j) ) = ( ( - p ) . ( ( ( i - j ) mod ( len ( - p ) ) ) + 1 ) )))
proof
